result.execSummary:
The defendant Corey D Corbisier was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Operate with Restricted Controlled Substance (3rd) [Modifiers: Penalty - Operating While under the Influence (3rd Offense)], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. Defendant Corey D Corbisier in court with attorney Christopher T. Froelich.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Minute sheet. State moves to amend Ct. 2 to Misdemeanor Possession of THC, gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to Ct. 1 and amended Ct. 2.  Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds pleas made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts pleas, and finds guilty of Ct. 1 and amended Ct. 2. Court dismisses Cts. 3, 4 & 15-TR-2235 but reads in for sentencing. State/Defense make joint sentencing recommendation. Defendant apologizes to the court, makes statement. Court makes statement, imposes sentence. Bond is no longer in effect.
